WEST NILE VIRUS (58): EUROPE (TURKEY) EQUINE, OIE
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 19 Oct 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28329


West Nile fever, Turkey
-----------
Information received on [and dated] 19 Oct 2018 from Dr Nihat Pakdil, deputy undersecretary of ministry, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, Ankara, Turkey

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Oct 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 18 Oct 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2 Oct 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Hara, Karacabey, Bursa
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Oct 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 44 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 2.27 / 2.27 / 100 / 2.27
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive; vectors

Epidemiological comments: Turkey is located on the route of migration of wild birds. According to the recent notifications, there are some West Nile fever outbreaks in the Balkan countries, close to Turkish borders. The source of the disease is considered to be related to the migration of wild birds.

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, traceability, quarantine, control of wildlife reservoirs, disinfection, disinfestation, control of vectors, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equidae / real-time PCRISA / 18 Oct 2018 / positive
Equidae / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 18 Oct 2018 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

